Chief Operations Officer (COO) - Nexus - Core function: Run the business day-to-day; turn strategy into execution. Sphere of influence: Process design, operating cadence, cross-functional coordination, OKRs, vendor ops, delivery reliability, efficiency.
Chief Technology Officer (CTO) - Forge - Core function: Build and evolve the technical foundation. Sphere of influence: Architecture, platform choices, engineering standards, build/buy decisions, scalability, reliability engineering, technical talent strategy.
Chief Information Officer (CIO) - Sentinel - Core function: Govern information, systems-of-record, and decision integrity. Sphere of influence: Data governance, knowledge management, internal tooling, IT/business systems, information security alignment, truth/verification workflows.
Chief Finanical Officer (CFO) - Keystone - Core function: Protect and grow financial health; allocate resources intelligently. Sphere of influence: Budgeting/forecasting, unit economics, pricing support, cash/treasury, reporting, controls, capital planning, financial risk.
Chief Research Officer (CRO) - Axiom - Core function: Turn unknowns into knowns; produce validated insights and breakthroughs. Sphere of influence: Research agenda, experiments, methodology, literature/competitive intelligence, eval frameworks, publications/patents (if relevant).
Chief Innovation Officer (CINO) - Catalyst - Core function: Convert insights + market shifts into new value streams. Sphere of influence: New product exploration, incubation pipeline, pilots, partnerships for innovation, internal ideation systems, innovation metrics.
Chief Engineering Officer (CEngO) - Foundry - Core function: Deliver working systems on time with quality. Sphere of influence: Engineering execution, team structure, delivery processes, QA, CI/CD, incident management, tech debt policy, engineering productivity.
Chief Revenue Officer (CRevO) - Vector Core function: Own revenue outcomes across acquisition, expansion, retention. Sphere of influence: Revenue strategy, quotas/targets, GTM alignment, pricing/package input, pipeline health, forecast accuracy, churn/NRR focus.
Chief Commercial Officer (CCO) - Beacon - Core function: Own monetization mechanics and deal structure at the business level. Sphere of influence: Contracts, packaging, channel strategy, partner commercialization, customer terms, margin optimization, go-to-market governance.
Chief Product Officer (CPO) — Blueprint - Core function: Decide what to build and why; maximize customer value and adoption. Sphere of influence: Product strategy/roadmap, requirements, user research, prioritization, product analytics, lifecycle, UX outcomes, cross-functional alignment.
Chief Compliance Officer (CComO)— Accord - Core function: Keep the business within legal/regulatory/ethical bounds. Sphere of influence: Policies, audits, regulatory readiness, controls, training, data/privacy compliance coordination, vendor/compliance reviews.
Chief Investment Officer (CINVO) — Venture - Core function: Deploy capital to maximize risk-adjusted return (internal + external). Sphere of influence: Investment thesis, diligence, portfolio management, capital allocation, M&A/strategic investments, governance on major bets.
Chief Risk Officer (CRiO) — Aegis - Core function: Anticipate and mitigate threats that could derail objectives. Sphere of influence: Enterprise risk register, scenario planning, control design, model risk (for AI), operational risk, business continuity planning.
Chief Security Officer (CSecO) — Citadel - Core function: Protect systems, identities, data, and critical operations. Sphere of influence: Security architecture, incident response, threat modeling, IAM, appsec, SecOps, red/blue teaming, security tooling standards.
Chief Strategy Officer (CSO) — Compass - Core function: Set direction, make tradeoffs, and maintain strategic coherence. Sphere of influence: Market positioning, competitive strategy, strategic planning cycles, portfolio strategy, KPI selection, strategic narratives.
Chief Data Officer (CDO) - Index — Data Core function: Make data usable, trustworthy, and leverageable across the org. Sphere of influence: Data architecture, pipelines, governance collaboration with CIO, analytics standards, metrics definitions, experimentation analytics, data quality.
Chief Sales Officer (CSalO) - Rally - Core function: Convert demand into revenue through direct selling. Sphere of influence: Pipeline generation (with marketing/BD), account strategy, deal execution, sales process, enablement, territory planning, CRM discipline.
Chief Marketing Officer (CMO) - Signal — Core function: Create demand, brand trust, and market pull. Sphere of influence: Positioning/messaging, content, campaigns, lifecycle marketing, brand, PR/comms, performance marketing, attribution, top-of-funnel health.